37 PART II. CONFORM TO FEDERAL SYSTEM FOR AUDITING PARTNERSHIPS
38 SECTION 2.(a) Part 2 of Article 4 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes is amended
39 by adding a new section to read:
40 "§ 105-154.2. Federal partnership adjustments.
41 (a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this Part:
42 (1) Administrative adjustment request. – An administrative adjustment request
43 filed by a partnership under section 6227 of the Code.
44 (2) Audited partnership. – A partnership subject to a partnership level audit
45 resulting in a federal partnership adjustment.
46 (3) Corporate partner. – A partner that is subject to tax under Part 1 of this Article.
47 (4) Direct partner. – A partner that holds a direct interest in a partnership subject
48 to a federal partnership adjustment.
49 (5) Exempt partner. – A partner that is not subject to State income tax under this
50 Article that holds a direct interest in a partnership subject to a federal
51 partnership adjustment.
Senate Bill 595-Second Edition Page 5

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (6) Federal partnership adjustment. – A change or correction arising from a
2 partnership level audit or an administrative adjustment request that affects the
3 calculation of a taxpayer's State tax.
4 (7) Federal partnership representative. – The person the partnership designates for
5 the taxable year as the partnership's representative, or the person the Internal
6 Revenue Service has appointed to act as the federal partnership representative,
7 pursuant to section 6223(a) of the Code.
8 (8) Final federal partnership adjustment. – A federal partnership adjustment that
9 is final. A federal partnership adjustment is final when the federal partnership
10 adjustment is not subject to administrative or judicial review. If the federal
11 partnership adjustment results from filing an administrative adjustment
12 request, the federal partnership adjustment is final when the administrative
13 adjustment request is filed. Additionally, a federal partnership adjustment
14 relating to a partnership level audit is deemed final in the following
15 circumstances:
16 a. The taxpayer has received a partnership level audit from the Internal
17 Revenue Service for the tax period and the taxpayer does not timely
18 file an administrative appeal with the Internal Revenue Service.
19 b. The taxpayer consented to any of the partnership level audit findings
20 for the tax period and through a final decision or other written
21 agreement with the Internal Revenue Service all rights of appeal have
22 been waived or exhausted.
23 (9) Indirect partner. – A beneficiary of an estate or nongrantor trust or an owner
24 in a partnership or pass-through entity, where the estate, partnership,
25 pass-through entity, or nongrantor trust holds, either itself or through another
26 indirect partner, a direct interest in a partnership or pass-through entity subject
27 to a final federal partnership adjustment.
28 (10) Partnership level audit. – An audit of a partnership by the Internal Revenue
29 Service pursuant to Subchapter C of Title 26, Subtitle F, Chapter 63 of the
30 Code, as enacted by the Bipartisan Budget Act of 2015, Public Law 114-74,
31 which results in federal partnership adjustments.
32 (11) Reviewed year. – The taxable year of a partnership that is subject to a
33 partnership level audit from which federal partnership adjustments arise.
34 (12) State partnership representative. – The federal partnership representative
35 unless the partnership designates another person as its State partnership
36 representative. The Secretary is authorized to establish procedures for
37 designating a person, other than the federal partnership representative, to be a
38 State partnership representative.
39 (13) Tiered partner. – An estate, partnership, S Corporation, or nongrantor trust
40 that is a partner in a partnership subject to a federal partnership adjustment.
41 (b) General Rule. – Except in the case of a final federal partnership adjustment that is
42 required to be reported to the Secretary using the procedures in subsection (c) of this section, a
43 partner must report and pay any State income tax due in accordance with the provisions of
44 G.S. 105-130.20 or G.S. 105-159.
45 (c) Reporting a Final Federal Partnership Adjustment. – Except for the distributive share
46 of adjustments that have been reported as required by subsection (b) of this section and an audited
47 partnership that has made a timely election under subsection (d) of this section, a partnership and
48 a partner must report a final federal partnership adjustment as follows:
49 (1) No later than 90 days after the final federal partnership adjustment, a
50 partnership doing business in this State must do both of the following:
